Comedian-cum-actor, Ayo Ajewole, popularly aka Woli Agba has lent his voice to domestic violence against women. He urged parents to advise their daughters appropriately. Nigerians have been discussing domestic violence, which they alleged was responsible for the death of popular gospel singer Osinachi Nwachukwu.   Leave if marriage becomes toxic-Dayo Amusa     Airport workers scramble for Portable’s money     Mr Macaroni to Kate Henshaw: your photo makes me vibrate   Woli Agba appealed to parents to tell their daughters they should not delay in leaving a failed marriage and returning to them. He warned there is a bigger chance of them being returning dead if they stay to endure such. The MC added any lady who dies enduring a failed marriage will definitely get replaced in no time. He wrote:“Teach your daughters that coming back home from a failed marriage is better than coming home in a coffin… If you die in the marriage, they will another to replace you immediately.”